WEBVTT

00:10.000 --> 00:22.000
You're Watching on 123Movies.to

00:41.250 --> 00:45.120
Long, long ago,
in a faraway land

00:45.290 --> 00:48.890
a young woodcarver took
secretly to the forest.

00:49.060 --> 00:54.050
His name was Geppetto,
and he was shy and quiet.

00:54.230 --> 00:56.600
Oh, and very much in love.

00:56.770 --> 00:59.600
I carve this heart
for dear Leona...

00:59.840 --> 01:02.070
while in this
peaceful meadow.

01:02.240 --> 01:04.640
With dreams and hope...

01:04.810 --> 01:07.110
my love endures.

01:07.280 --> 01:10.510
Forever yours, Geppetto.

01:11.750 --> 01:15.080
Sooner or later, though,
when the heart is full...

01:15.250 --> 01:17.590
and the heavens are listening,

01:17.760 --> 01:21.190
magic... is bound to happen.

01:45.020 --> 01:49.720
For many years after,
Geppetto kept to his chores,

01:49.890 --> 01:52.760
and the forest
kept Geppetto's secret.

01:52.920 --> 01:56.880
But the forest knew one thing
that Geppetto did not:

01:57.060 --> 02:00.230
that miracles
don't grow on trees.

02:00.400 --> 02:03.560
Miracles are made
in the heart

02:21.150 --> 02:24.710
A log underneath the wheel.

02:24.890 --> 02:27.450
Oh, I got to take you home.

02:27.630 --> 02:30.030
A very good one, too.

02:30.200 --> 02:31.420
All right.

02:32.530 --> 02:33.900
Here we go.

02:40.110 --> 02:43.970
@ My wife's the blushing,
blooming rose of dawning

02:44.140 --> 02:45.470
@ Without the sting

02:45.640 --> 02:47.130
Morning, Luigi

02:47.310 --> 02:49.080
Put a sock in it, Luigi!

02:49.250 --> 02:51.080
@ Welcome, welcome

02:51.250 --> 02:52.840
@ Blessed morning sun

02:53.020 --> 02:54.250
@ Welcome, welcome

02:54.420 --> 02:55.410
@ New day just begun

02:55.590 --> 02:56.650
@ Buon giorno, life

02:56.820 --> 02:58.120
@ Buon giorno, sun

02:58.290 --> 02:59.620
@ Buon giorno, wife

02:59.790 --> 03:01.190
@ My Little one

03:01.360 --> 03:02.660
@ That's my little song

03:02.830 --> 03:05.020
@ Good day,
buon giorno, everyone

03:05.200 --> 03:06.690
@ Housework, homework

03:06.870 --> 03:08.530
@ Off to work we go

03:08.700 --> 03:10.360
@ Buying, selling

03:10.540 --> 03:12.400
@ Making money so that we can eat

03:12.570 --> 03:13.540
@ And we can drink

03:13.710 --> 03:16.770
@ and we can have a little fun

03:16.940 --> 03:18.070
@ I've sung my little song

03:18.240 --> 03:20.110
@ And now my little song is done

03:23.680 --> 03:25.480
@ Buon giorno, Life,
buon giorno, sun

03:25.650 --> 03:28.410
@ Buon giorno, wife,
my little one

03:28.590 --> 03:30.080
@ That's my little song

03:30.260 --> 03:33.250
@ Good day,
buon giorno, everyone

03:34.990 --> 03:36.120
Watch this

03:39.400 --> 03:41.190
Oops, looks like you've
dropped your wood,

03:41.370 --> 03:42.230
Signor Puppetmaker.

03:42.400 --> 03:44.390
Maybe I should be
more careful next time

03:46.100 --> 03:47.090
Let's go boys.

03:47.270 --> 03:49.500
Hey, last one to the bridge
gets dunked.

03:56.880 --> 03:58.870
Yoo hoo, everybody.

03:59.050 --> 04:00.680
I'm home.

04:02.850 --> 04:04.750
All right, don't say hello.

04:07.090 --> 04:08.420
Hello, little one.

04:08.590 --> 04:09.920
How was your day?

04:10.100 --> 04:11.890
Ah, that's nice. Me...

04:12.060 --> 04:14.360
I got lost in the forest.

04:14.530 --> 04:18.730
Used to be a time
when west was west.

04:18.899 --> 04:20.560
Are you two fighting again?

04:20.740 --> 04:23.400
What's the problem this time?

04:23.580 --> 04:26.200
He said I have a funny nose.

04:26.380 --> 04:28.440
I said you have a funny toes.

04:28.610 --> 04:29.710
Funny nose.

04:29.880 --> 04:31.040
Funny toes.

04:31.220 --> 04:33.840
Now stop it. I'm tired of
hearing you two argue.

04:34.020 --> 04:35.490
Stop it!

04:36.760 --> 04:39.780
You know what happens
to bad little boys who fight?

04:39.960 --> 04:43.050
They go to bed
without being sandpapered.

04:45.860 --> 04:47.350
It's chilly.

04:54.740 --> 04:55.870
There.

04:56.040 --> 04:58.670
It's going to be a chilly night.

05:11.990 --> 05:15.190
This log has a will of it's own.

05:23.430 --> 05:26.930
Let's see if we can find
a face to match.

05:43.220 --> 05:45.420
Our heart.

05:45.590 --> 05:49.080
Anyone who wants a new brother,
say so now.

05:49.260 --> 05:53.160
All right, all right,
don't everybody talk at once.

05:55.870 --> 05:58.930
I'm going to make
the most perfect nose.

06:02.510 --> 06:06.500
A world of wisdom
could be told in a nose.

06:55.330 --> 06:58.450
Open wide.
Give me a big smile.

07:17.220 --> 07:20.670
Nina, go find yourself a mouse.

07:43.810 --> 07:47.210
Blue eyes, just like your papa.

07:53.350 --> 07:55.950
Bellissimo.

07:58.090 --> 08:01.750
Now would you like your papa
to show you how to walk?

08:02.530 --> 08:03.550
Yes?

08:05.200 --> 08:08.460
Very nice.
What a smart little boy you are.

08:08.630 --> 08:10.730
Excuse me, coming through!

08:10.900 --> 08:13.030
Now say hello
to your brothers and sisters.

08:13.200 --> 08:14.470
Say hello.

08:14.640 --> 08:17.670
They'll keep you company
while I'm at work.

08:17.840 --> 08:21.370
Now what shall we call you,
dear child, hmm?

08:21.550 --> 08:23.570
You're made of pine.

08:23.750 --> 08:25.580
That's a start.

08:28.250 --> 08:30.190
You have beautiful eyes.

08:30.360 --> 08:33.289
Occhi magnifico.

08:35.360 --> 08:37.520
We'll call you...

08:39.200 --> 08:40.960
Pinocchio!

08:42.570 --> 08:44.000
Pinocchio.

08:49.770 --> 08:52.070
Better to have puppets...

08:52.240 --> 08:57.040
than noisy little boys
running around.

09:01.620 --> 09:04.110
Oh, my back is...

09:11.260 --> 09:14.320
I'm not as young
as I used to be.

10:15.530 --> 10:17.320
Nina, leave that puppet alone!

10:17.500 --> 10:19.690
Behave yourself!

10:41.990 --> 10:45.650
Excuse me,
coming through.

11:09.810 --> 11:11.440
Ah, get the soap.

11:22.930 --> 11:24.860
Thank you.
Now get me the scrub brush.

11:25.030 --> 11:26.660
Scwub-bwsh.

11:39.340 --> 11:41.470
It's happened.

11:41.650 --> 11:44.140
I've finally lost my mind.

11:44.320 --> 11:45.780
Mind...

11:47.850 --> 11:49.440
It's impossible!

11:51.490 --> 11:52.890
You can't be real!

11:53.060 --> 11:54.750
Real.

11:54.930 --> 11:56.590
But you're a puppet!

11:58.630 --> 12:00.320
Pup-peh...

12:01.800 --> 12:02.860
Pa-pa!

12:03.030 --> 12:06.060
No, I'm not your papa!

12:10.140 --> 12:11.340
Wait, Pinocchio.

12:12.340 --> 12:12.670
Stop!

12:16.480 --> 12:19.310
Come down right now!

12:19.480 --> 12:20.970
What are you doing?

12:22.920 --> 12:25.320
Come down this instant,
young... man.

12:25.490 --> 12:26.850
Come down here!

12:27.020 --> 12:28.720
I'm not going to go
chasing after you.

13:34.330 --> 13:36.560
Luigi, please, put a sock in it!

13:43.070 --> 13:44.830
Pinocchio, hold on, I'll save you!

14:11.000 --> 14:12.090
No!

14:27.610 --> 14:30.640
Take off my underwear right now!

14:33.680 --> 14:36.020
Pinocchio, listen to me.

14:36.390 --> 14:37.450
Pinocchio?

14:37.490 --> 14:38.960
Right. Listen to me.

14:39.120 --> 14:40.520
Papa.

14:40.690 --> 14:42.220
No, l--No, that's not--

14:42.390 --> 14:44.220
Well, yes,
in a manner of speaking.

14:44.400 --> 14:46.120
No, I'm not your papa.

14:46.160 --> 14:47.930
Papa, papa, papa...

14:47.970 --> 14:50.020
You are a puppet.
You're not a real boy.

14:50.200 --> 14:51.430
Real boy.

14:51.600 --> 14:53.500
No! And be glad for it.

14:53.670 --> 14:55.730
If you were a real boy,

14:55.910 --> 14:58.970
you'd have to have doctor
instead of--

14:59.140 --> 15:01.370
Sit still!

15:01.550 --> 15:04.980
Look at this mess! I'll have
to wash all over again.

15:05.150 --> 15:06.670
Ciao, Geppetto.

15:06.850 --> 15:08.940
Quite a new puppet.

15:09.120 --> 15:10.610
He's amazing.

15:10.790 --> 15:11.950
He still needs work.

15:12.120 --> 15:14.850
So do you. Look at you,
you were up all night again.

15:15.030 --> 15:18.360
- I slept a little.
- You were up all night.

15:18.530 --> 15:22.060
I made these
for Lorenzini's puppets,

15:22.230 --> 15:24.430
but I think he needs them more.

15:24.600 --> 15:25.430
Thank you.

15:25.600 --> 15:27.130
You're welcome.

15:27.300 --> 15:29.600
Wouldn't want
his head to fry, either.

15:29.770 --> 15:30.600
Thank you.

15:30.780 --> 15:32.000
You're welcome.

15:32.180 --> 15:34.080
Bet your house
is full of sawdust.

15:34.250 --> 15:35.340
I'll come by and sweep it up.

15:35.510 --> 15:36.980
Leona, I'm not a child.

15:37.150 --> 15:39.010
The Little one,
does he have a name?

15:39.180 --> 15:40.550
Pinocchio.

15:40.720 --> 15:43.020
Enchanted.

15:43.190 --> 15:44.550
Leona

15:44.660 --> 15:46.150
Leona...

15:52.430 --> 15:54.900
You even gave him your heart.

15:55.070 --> 15:56.430
Our heart

15:56.600 --> 15:58.230
What did you say?

15:58.400 --> 16:00.800
Nothing.

16:00.970 --> 16:02.530
Come, Pinocchio.

16:02.710 --> 16:05.170
Come, Pinocchio.
Come, Papa.

16:09.780 --> 16:11.770
Seems a little stiff, Leona.

16:11.950 --> 16:14.110
Just like his father.

16:20.620 --> 16:23.020
Marco, look!

16:23.190 --> 16:24.290
Look here.

16:24.460 --> 16:26.660
Wow! Look at that.

16:38.240 --> 16:39.570
Wow!

17:00.260 --> 17:01.730
Stop it!

17:21.390 --> 17:23.079
What are you doing?

17:23.250 --> 17:24.220
It's your color.

17:24.390 --> 17:27.319
- Did I ask for a scarf?
- No.

17:27.490 --> 17:29.120
Then get rid of it.

17:29.290 --> 17:30.820
I'll take that one.

17:33.800 --> 17:36.320
He's magnificent, Geppetto!

17:36.500 --> 17:38.800
Do you see what I see?

17:38.840 --> 17:39.860
Yes!

17:40.870 --> 17:43.470
What?

17:43.640 --> 17:45.800
He is more than--
he's just--

17:45.980 --> 17:47.140
he's...

17:47.310 --> 17:48.470
Well, l--well...

17:48.650 --> 17:49.910
How did you do this?

17:50.080 --> 17:51.010
I don't know.

17:51.180 --> 17:52.150
Where are the strings? l--

17:52.320 --> 17:53.150
I don't know.

17:53.320 --> 17:54.250
You don't know.

17:54.420 --> 17:57.820
I don't know.
Tino, am I going crazy?

17:57.990 --> 18:00.510
I have no idea
how this happened.

18:00.690 --> 18:02.560
They're going to
burn me at the stake!

18:02.730 --> 18:05.990
No, no,
they've stopped burning people.

18:06.160 --> 18:08.150
They might hang you, though.

18:11.140 --> 18:12.600
Excuse me, coming through.

18:12.770 --> 18:14.260
Then you'll know where
the strings are.

18:27.650 --> 18:30.620
Are you real boy?

18:30.790 --> 18:33.220
Yes. Are you?

18:33.960 --> 18:34.980
Yes

19:03.120 --> 19:05.210
Hello

19:05.260 --> 19:06.690
Hello

19:07.860 --> 19:11.760
Oh, my, what an intriguing
little item you are.

19:11.930 --> 19:13.120
May l?

19:16.400 --> 19:18.830
Empty as a witch's dowry.

19:19.000 --> 19:24.130
Oh, and look how smoothly
his arms move.

19:24.310 --> 19:26.070
Volpe, Felinet...

19:28.250 --> 19:32.110
Excuse me, but haven't you two
got a pushcart to rob?

19:32.280 --> 19:34.150
We've already done that.

19:35.750 --> 19:36.740
Come, Pinocchio.

19:36.920 --> 19:40.860
Oh, but, Geppetto, darling,
we were just playing with him.

19:41.030 --> 19:42.220
He'll play with
his own sort, thank you.

19:42.390 --> 19:44.830
And what sort would that be?

19:46.530 --> 19:50.090
Pinocchio, don't
wander away like that.

19:50.270 --> 19:52.130
I don't want you to do that.

19:52.300 --> 19:56.170
I don't get it.
ls he a boy or a puppet?

19:56.340 --> 19:59.970
He's a puppet, furface,
and he's worth a fortune.

20:00.140 --> 20:03.270
And I know exactly
where to cash him in.

20:03.450 --> 20:06.280
Don't worry, son,
I'll get your ball back.

20:09.850 --> 20:13.080
Take my kid's ball, would you?

20:38.580 --> 20:40.710
Listen closely.

20:40.880 --> 20:42.910
Next week's puppet show...

20:43.090 --> 20:45.420
must be the most
spectacular ever.

20:45.590 --> 20:48.850
Every single boy
must be in attendance.

20:49.030 --> 20:51.650
Lorenzini, darling.

20:51.830 --> 20:54.260
Felinet, looking for employment?

20:54.430 --> 20:57.630
I see my timing is purr-fect!

20:57.800 --> 20:59.830
What I've seen
will assure you...

21:00.000 --> 21:03.630
more curtain calls
than Rome has rats.

21:03.810 --> 21:05.830
Do tell.

21:06.010 --> 21:08.670
There, there. That's better.

21:08.850 --> 21:11.280
That's didn't hurt, did it?

21:11.450 --> 21:13.010
No. Didn't hurt.

21:19.160 --> 21:20.750
What does he want?

21:23.760 --> 21:25.230
Open up.

21:25.400 --> 21:26.990
No good can come of this.

21:27.160 --> 21:29.130
Be very quiet.
Stay here and be quiet

21:32.440 --> 21:34.870
Don't even breathe.

21:35.040 --> 21:36.400
Do you understand?

21:36.570 --> 21:37.470
Open up!

21:37.640 --> 21:40.970
Signor Lorenzini, uh...

21:42.050 --> 21:43.640
Geppetto, my friend.

21:43.810 --> 21:47.150
To want do I owe this honor?

21:47.320 --> 21:50.840
The honor is mine
to call a gain on the man...

21:51.020 --> 21:52.610
with the magical hands.

21:52.790 --> 21:54.380
I bring good news, Geppetto.

21:54.560 --> 21:58.050
I am mounting my grandest
production ever,

21:58.230 --> 22:03.500
and I want to purchase
your newest creation...

22:05.070 --> 22:07.130
whatever that might be.

22:12.580 --> 22:15.980
I've been spending a great deal
of time in the forest lately.

22:16.150 --> 22:20.450
I will carve you something very
special the first chance I get.

22:22.150 --> 22:26.610
I was looking
for something with,

22:26.790 --> 22:30.690
shall we say, thinner strings.

22:30.860 --> 22:32.350
Thinner strings?

22:32.530 --> 22:35.520
Why-- why didn't
you say so? Come.

22:35.700 --> 22:37.830
I've got just the thing.

22:38.000 --> 22:41.160
These wonderful pieces
are made of cherry wood,

22:41.340 --> 22:45.040
and they are on sale
this week only.

22:45.210 --> 22:47.700
Don't toy with me.

22:47.880 --> 22:51.210
I didn't buy those puppets
from you two years ago,

22:51.380 --> 22:54.680
and I'm not going to
buy them today,

22:54.850 --> 22:57.620
so show me your best...

22:57.790 --> 22:59.850
and show me now.

23:08.730 --> 23:10.890
Excuse me. Coming through.

23:12.270 --> 23:15.710
Incredible.

23:15.870 --> 23:17.770
He is perfect.

23:20.080 --> 23:21.440
Stay.

23:21.610 --> 23:24.100
- Boys do little bugs.
- Bugs

23:24.150 --> 23:27.610
Don't they?
They like to tease them...

23:27.780 --> 23:29.580
and twist them and--

23:29.750 --> 23:30.980
Please, Lorenzini.

23:33.390 --> 23:36.950
Name your price.

23:37.130 --> 23:38.750
He's not for sale.

23:38.930 --> 23:42.390
- Geppetto, everything is for sale.
- Stay, Stay!

23:42.570 --> 23:45.030
Not him.
Not at any price.

23:45.200 --> 23:46.670
Stay, bug.

24:06.890 --> 24:10.990
You can have the emperor
and his daughter, and that's it.

24:14.560 --> 24:17.690
You are making a big mistake,
Geppetto.

24:20.670 --> 24:23.970
That's my last offer.
Take it or leave it.

24:27.310 --> 24:28.540
Very well.

24:33.150 --> 24:37.280
I will take these lovely puppets
off your hands.

24:37.450 --> 24:41.650
I'm just burning with ideas.

24:41.830 --> 24:45.350
Thank you.
Good afternoon, Geppetto.

24:51.700 --> 24:52.730
Pinocchio.

24:55.210 --> 24:56.300
Pinocchio

25:06.750 --> 25:08.480
Infantino is a creep.

25:12.190 --> 25:13.710
Hey, fatty!

25:24.630 --> 25:26.760
You're late, dimwit.

25:37.180 --> 25:40.120
Pinocchio, show
yourself right now...

25:40.280 --> 25:42.910
because I'm not leaving this
house to look for you again.

25:44.050 --> 25:46.320
Would someone please
like to tell us...

25:46.490 --> 25:49.820
of a characteristic
which separates humans...

25:49.990 --> 25:52.290
from the rest of
the animal kingdom?

25:52.460 --> 25:54.050
Cages.

25:54.230 --> 25:56.030
Humans cry tears, professore.

25:56.200 --> 25:58.860
Ah, tears.

26:00.370 --> 26:02.070
Expressions of the soul.

26:02.240 --> 26:05.770
Do any other creatures look
so deeply within themselves?

26:09.280 --> 26:11.940
No, professore. Only humans.

26:12.120 --> 26:14.740
We must always decide
what is right and wrong.

26:14.920 --> 26:15.910
Excellent.

26:26.260 --> 26:28.060
Hey, Woody.

26:28.230 --> 26:29.720
You ever get termites?

26:29.900 --> 26:32.490
What are termites?

26:32.670 --> 26:33.830
They're bugs.

26:34.000 --> 26:36.500
I like bugs.

26:36.670 --> 26:39.040
Not these kind, you don't.

26:39.210 --> 26:41.940
They eat wood like you.

26:46.920 --> 26:50.650
Hey, lay off my friend, Woody.

26:50.820 --> 26:52.950
Lay off my friend, Woody.

26:55.190 --> 26:57.290
What is going on
in my classroom?

27:00.700 --> 27:03.790
The new kid punched Lampwick,
professore.

27:13.910 --> 27:16.710
ls that true?

27:21.550 --> 27:22.610
No

27:27.860 --> 27:30.350
Hey, how'd you do that?

27:30.530 --> 27:32.150
Silence.

27:32.330 --> 27:36.820
Now, you're not lying to me
by any slim chance, are you?

27:49.210 --> 27:51.980
There are two kinds of lies--

27:52.150 --> 27:56.210
lies that have short legs
and lies that have a long nose,

27:56.390 --> 28:00.580
and yours are clearly the kind
that have long nose.

28:00.760 --> 28:05.290
Now, I will give you one
last chance to redeem yourself.

28:05.460 --> 28:10.300
If you didn't punch Lampwick,
how did he end up on the floor?

28:12.740 --> 28:16.100
Nobody punched Lampwick.

28:16.270 --> 28:19.330
Lampwick punched himself.

28:21.080 --> 28:25.140
l--l mean, a man climed
in the window and punched him.

28:25.320 --> 28:27.720
And Lampwick tried
to kick him back,

28:27.880 --> 28:30.110
but he missed and fell
on the floor, and--

28:38.760 --> 28:40.090
Silence.

28:41.600 --> 28:42.620
Infantino!

28:47.100 --> 28:48.230
Silence!

28:55.680 --> 28:59.780
Infantino, go on, go on.

28:59.950 --> 29:02.320
Handkerchief. Go on, quickly.

29:02.490 --> 29:05.820
Run, run, run, run, run!

29:28.280 --> 29:33.440
Right, I did punch Lampwick,
professore,

29:33.620 --> 29:36.590
and I'm sorry

29:36.750 --> 29:39.480
Well, it's too late
for that now.

29:39.660 --> 29:41.920
If there's one thing
l will not tolerate...

29:42.090 --> 29:44.460
in my classroom, it's a liar.

29:45.530 --> 29:46.890
Out.

29:53.240 --> 29:54.860
And...

29:55.040 --> 29:56.970
I'm sorry that
l kicked him, too.

29:57.140 --> 29:58.970
Out.

30:04.250 --> 30:08.380
And I'm even more sorry
that I told a lie.

30:08.550 --> 30:10.540
Out, out, I said.

30:10.720 --> 30:14.020
But I want to stay and learn.

30:14.190 --> 30:18.650
Now, class, we will review
what we have learned today.

30:30.470 --> 30:31.870
If anything happened to him,

30:32.040 --> 30:33.510
